---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy and Terms of Service">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl p-4 md:p-8">
    <h1 class="mb-10 text-3xl font-bold">Privacy Policy and Terms of Service</h1>
    <section class="mb-6">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">1. Data Privacy</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>No Data Collection:</strong> 2FA Authenticator does not collect, store, or share any personal information or
        user data. All application data is stored directly in your browser or in your Google Drive account.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Google Drive Access:</strong> 2FA Authenticator requires access to your Google Drive account solely to
        synchronize your tokens. This access is used only to allow you to retrieve and use your tokens from any compatible
        device. 2FA Authenticator does not store any information from your Google account, except for the credentials needed
        to upload files to your Drive and the folder identifier where backups are stored. We do not access, read, or store
        any other type of information from your Google Drive account.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-6">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">2. Terms of Service</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Free Use:</strong> 2FA Authenticator is free to use. There are no charges, and we do not require any form of
        payment to use it.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>No Warranties:</strong> 2FA Authenticator is provided "as is" without any warranties of any kind. We do not
        guarantee that it is error-free or suitable for any particular purpose. Use of the application is at your own risk.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Limitation of Liability:</strong> In no event shall the application be liable for any direct, indirect,
        incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of the application.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-6">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">3. Token Synchronization</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Token synchronization is securely performed through your Google Drive account. It is your responsibility to secure
        your Google account and the devices on which you use the application.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you choose to delete the application or revoke access to Google Drive, the tokens stored in your Google Drive will
        remain there until you manually delete them.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-6">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">4. Security</h2>
      <p>
        2FA Authenticator implements security measures to protect your data stored in Google Drive. However, remember that
        the security of your tokens also depends on the steps you take to protect your Google account and your device.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-6">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">5. Modifications to this Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy and Terms of Service at any time. Modifications will be effective
        immediately after being posted on this page. It is your responsibility to review this page periodically to stay
        informed of any changes.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">6. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy and Terms of Service, you can contact us at <a
          href="mailto:2fa_authenticator@googlegroups.com"
          class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">2fa_authenticator@googlegroups.com</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
